==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shrouded
<hw>Shroud"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Provided with a shroud or
shrouds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Shrouded gear</b></col> <fld>(Mach.)</fld>, <cd>a
cogwheel or pinion having flanges which form closed ends to the spaces
between the teeth and thus strengthen the teeth by tying them
together.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shrouding</ent>⟦br⟧
